THE CHOOSE COLLEGE EDUCATIONAL FOUNDATION PRIDES ITSELF IN OUTREACHING TO TARGETED POPULATIONS AND REACHING INTO COMMUNITIES THAT HAVE HISTORICALLY BEEN MARGINALIZED, UNDER-SERVED AND DISENFRANCHISED FROM THE RESOURCES AND INFORMATION NECESSARY TO MAKE INFORMED DECISIONS ABOUT THEIR COLLEGE GOING OPTIONS. TO DO THIS WORK, CCEF PARTNERS AND COLLABORATES WITH A WIDE SPECTRUM OF THE GENERAL PUBLIC, INCLUDING AND NOT LIMITED TO, PUBLIC K-12 SCHOOLS, PUBLIC AND PRIVATE COLLEGE AND UNIVERSITIES, COMMUNITY GROUPS, FAITH-BASED ORGANIZATIONS, SOCIAL SERVICE PROVIDERS, AND INDIVIDUALS COMMITTED TO SUPPORTING WITH THEIR TIME, TALENT, AND TREASURES TO SUPPORT CCEF SERVICE GOALS AND OUTCOMES. THE CCEF GOVERNING BOARD REPRESENTS A BROAD SPECTRUM OF THE CCEF COMMUNITY REPRESENTED BY CURRENT AND RETIRED PUBLIC SCHOOL EDUCATORS AND ADMINISTRATORS, A RETIRED COLLEGE PRESIDENT, A LEADER IN THE FAITH COMMUNITY, AND SMALL BUSINESS OWNERS. THROUGH TRADITIONAL AND NON-TRADITIONAL OUTREACH EFFORTS AND BY REQUEST FROM MULTIPLE SUPPORTERS, CCEF HAS RECENTLY BROADENED ITS FOOTPRINT BEYOND THE COMMUNITY IT RESIDES IN BY LAUNCHING A NATIONAL MEMBERSHIP PROGRAM. THE BENEFITS OF THIS MEMBERSHIP PROGRAM INCLUDE THE PROVISION OF INFORMATION GUIDES TO FAMILIES, PROFESSIONAL DEVELOPMENT FOR SCHOOL EDUCATORS, AND OPPORTUNITIES TO SUPPORT CHILDREN AND THEIR FAMILIES AS THEY PURSUE HIGHER EDUCATION. THE ORGANIZATION HAS ENROLLED 75 FAMILIES IN ITS MEMBERSHIP PROGRAM SINCE THE PROGRAM WAS LAUNCHED IN 2015.
